## PRACTICAL LAB 1 — Deploy Apache on Windows (Unit I)

**Scenario:** Pull Apache httpd, run on port 8081, verify in browser.

**Step 1 — Pull image:**
```powershell
docker pull httpd:alpine
```

![Pulling httpd:alpine from Docker Hub](../assets/screenshots/unit-1/01-docker-pull-httpd.svg)
*Pulling httpd:alpine from Docker Hub — captured on Windows PowerShell + Docker Desktop*


**Step 2 — Run container:**
```powershell
docker run -d --name apache-lab -p 8081:80 httpd:alpine
```

![Starting Apache container](../assets/screenshots/unit-1/03-docker-run-apache.svg)
*Starting Apache container — captured on Windows PowerShell + Docker Desktop*


**Step 3 — Verify:**
```powershell
docker ps
curl.exe http://localhost:8081
```

![Running containers with port mapping](../assets/screenshots/unit-1/04-docker-ps.svg)
*Running containers with port mapping — captured on Windows PowerShell + Docker Desktop*


![HTTP response from Apache](../assets/screenshots/unit-1/05-curl-apache.svg)
*HTTP response from Apache — captured on Windows PowerShell + Docker Desktop*


**Step 4 — Inspect port mapping:**
```powershell
docker inspect apache-lab --format "{{.NetworkSettings.Ports}}"
```

**Step 5 — Cleanup:**
```powershell
docker stop apache-lab
docker rm apache-lab
```

